# English version

## Project Overview  
Cockpit_Drone is an application developed 
in Object Pascal (Lazarus/Free Pascal) for remote drone control and monitoring. It integrates joystick, GPS serial input, camera and 
map components, providing a central GUI for real-time interaction, communication configurations and efficient drone control.

## 
Project Structure  

- **main.pas** — Main GUI to manage joystick, drone, GPS, camera, and map control and monitoring.  
- 
**config.pas** — Communication parameters and joystick configuration form with real-time input visualization.  
- 
**conectioncx10w.pas** — TCP/UDP communication manager for CX10W drone with handshake and joystick data transmission.  
- 
**gps.pas** — GPS serial reading, NMEA sentence decoding and display of location and signal quality.  
- **camera.pas** — Visual 
form for camera data, with no implemented logic yet.  
- **map.pas** — Form for map display using grid component, pending logic 
implementation.  
- **funcs.pas** — Contains `MAPA` function for linear analog value mapping to byte range.

## Features  

- Real-time 
drone control via joystick.  
- Flexible serial and network communication parameters.  
- GPS data processing and display.  
- Robust 
TCP/UDP communication with drone.  
- Initial visual interfaces for camera and map.  
- Analog signal normalization utility.

## Current 
Status  

- Basic device integration and infrastructure functional.  
- Working main UI and configuration modules.  
- Camera, map, and 
joystick modules lack functional code.  
- MAPA function lacks robust error checking.  
- Further development recommended for 
exception handling, robustness, and feature completion.

## Installation

Follow the same steps as in Portuguese section.

## Contact

Please contact by email or WhatsApp as above.

## License

Free use, modification and distribution under terms defined by developers; 
see maintainers for details.

## Official Site

See Brazilian URL above.

